
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dcmd` (Docker Compose Management Tool) baraye modiriyat asan-tar va sari'tar container-haye Docker estefade mishavad. In dastoor komak mikonad ta shoma service-ha ra ba yek dastoor start, stop, va update konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dcmd up`     --> 🚀 Ejra kardane hameye service-ha tarif shode dar file docker-compose.yml.
    🔹 `dcmd down`   --> ⛔ Stop kardane hameye service-ha va pak kardane container-ha.
    🔹 `dcmd restart`--> 🔄 Restart kardane hameye service-ha.
    🔹 `dcmd logs`   --> 🪵 Namayesh log-haye hameye service-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dcmd up

    🔹 Ejra kardane hameye service-ha.

    $ dcmd down

    🔹 Stop va remove kardane hameye service-ha.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dcmd up -d
    
    🔹 Ejra kardane service-ha dar background (detached mode), be in mani ke terminal shoma azad mimanad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dcmd` (Docker Compose Management Tool) command is used for easier and faster management of Docker containers. This command helps you start, stop, and update services with a single command.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dcmd up`     --> 🚀 Run all the services defined in the docker-compose.yml file.
    🔹 `dcmd down`   --> ⛔ Stop all the services and remove the containers.
    🔹 `dcmd restart`--> 🔄 Restart all the services.
    🔹 `dcmd logs`   --> 🪵 Show the logs for all the services.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dcmd up

    🔹 Run all the services.

    $ dcmd down

    🔹 Stop and remove all the services.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dcmd up -d

    🔹 Run the services in the background (detached mode), meaning your terminal will remain free.

